Plan the implementation of E5: Session Persistence & Undo Framework for a browser-based DAW (BRUTALWAV).

## Epic Description
Zod session schema with version field for all session state (R-UBI-11). Draft-then-swap IndexedDB persistence pattern (write session_draft, on success rename to session_current, backup to session_backup). Save queue serialization (max one IDB write in-flight, INV-4). Auto-save every 30s with debounce during rapid edits. Session recovery dialog for malformed JSON (R-UNW-08): parse each section independently, load valid, discard invalid. Undo/redo command framework: Command interface (type, execute, undo, serialize). Command registry for domain epics to register command types. Bounded undo stack (200 entries) with buffer reference eviction. Session browser UI (list saved sessions, load, delete, rename). Ctrl+S keyboard shortcut. EARS: R-EVT-13, R-UBI-07, R-UBI-11, R-UNW-06, R-UNW-08, NFR-08, NFR-15. Interface exports: SessionSchema, Command, UndoManager. QA: round-trip serialization, concurrent save handling, schema migration.

## Current Codebase State

### Store (src/state/store.ts)
```typescript
export type TransportState = "stopped" | "playing" | "paused";
export type AudioEngineStatus = "uninitialized" | "suspended" | "running" | "error";
export type DawStore = {
  transportState: TransportState;
  bpm: number;
  cursorSeconds: number;
  loopEnabled: boolean;
  loopStart: number;
  loopEnd: number;
  engineStatus: AudioEngineStatus;
  // ... actions
};
export const useDawStore = create<DawStore>()((set) => ({ ... }));
```

### Existing IndexedDB Pattern (src/audio/media-pool/idb-storage.ts)
- Storage interface pattern with in-memory + IDB implementations
- Lazy DB initialization
- Promise-based operations

### Existing Command Registry (src/ui/keyboard/command-registry.ts)
```typescript
export type Command = {
  id: string;
  label: string;
  execute: () => void;
  enabled?: () => boolean;
};
export class CommandRegistry { ... }
```

### Shortcut Map (src/ui/keyboard/shortcut-map.ts)
```typescript
export type ShortcutBinding = {
  key: string;
  ctrl?: boolean; shift?: boolean; alt?: boolean; meta?: boolean;
  commandId: string;
};
export class ShortcutMap { ... }
```

### TypeScript: Strict mode, noUncheckedIndexedAccess, exactOptionalPropertyTypes
### Path aliases: @/* -> src/*, @state/* -> src/state/*
### Test runner: Vitest 4.1.1 with jsdom
### Dependencies: React 19, Zustand 5, NO Zod yet (needs installing)
### Pattern: Colocated tests (*.test.ts next to source)

## Key Constraints
1. TDD: Tests FIRST, then implementation
2. Follow existing patterns (discriminated result types, async init, in-memory test storage)
3. Minimal, lean code -- no over-engineering
4. Zod needs to be added as a dependency
5. The existing Command type in command-registry.ts is different from the undo Command -- the undo Command needs execute/undo/serialize. Plan carefully how to extend or compose.

## Plan Requirements
Create a step-by-step implementation plan with:
1. File structure for new code
2. Order of implementation (what depends on what)
3. Test strategy for each module
4. Integration points with existing code

Keep it LEAN. The minimum viable implementation that satisfies the epic description.

